OL,3,CThe 'quiet' hospital ward helping new
OL,4,Cmums and babies get home faster
OL,6,FJosie Dodgeson, the deputy director of
OL,7,Fmidwifery, admits before the noise on
OL,8,Fthe ward was 'chaotic' and there was a
OL,9,F"heightened atmosphere" for staff.
OL,11,F"The minute the silent call-bell
OL,12,Fsystem went in there was an air of
OL,13,Fcalm," she said.
OL,15,F"It was visibly noticeable as you
OL,16,Fwalked on the ward and you almost
OL,17,Flowered your voice when you introduced
OL,18,Fyourself to people."
OL,20,FKath Bell, the ward manager, describes
OL,21,Fhow the app works.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
